To create a program, you need a Linux terminal or its alternative and the make utility

If you don't have make try
    
    $ sudo apt install make


Enter 
    
    $ make sorter

to make programs


sorter-en sorts texts in Russian and sorter-ru sorts texts in English


To test the programs you can do

    $ ./sorter-en hamlet

to sort Hamlet by Shakespeare or

    $ ./sorter-ru onegin

to sort Evgeniy Onegin by Pushkin



You can find the results of the program in the directory results

